== Find Keywords ==
Create folder <code>~/bin</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
mkdir ~/bin
}}

Create a file <code>~/bin/mygrep</code>. Paste the following.

{{CodeSelect|code=
#!/bin/bash
set -x
exec \
grep \
--exclude=README.md \
--exclude=GPLv2 \
--exclude=GPLv3 \
--exclude=COPYING \
--exclude=changelog.upstream-old1 \
--exclude-dir=mnt \
--exclude-dir=qubes-src/linux-template-builder/mnt \
--exclude=changelog.upstream \
--exclude-dir=".git" \
--exclude-dir=chroot-debian \
--exclude-dir=chroot-buster "$@"
}}

Save.

Make executable.

{{CodeSelect|code=
chmod +x ~/bin/mygrep
}}

Change directory.

{{CodeSelect|code=
cd {{project_name_short}}
}}

Search for string. For example <code>grub-pc</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
mygrep -r -i grub-pc
}}

== Find Files ==
Create folder <code>~/bin</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
mkdir ~/bin
}}

Create a file <code>~/bin/myfind</code>. Paste the following.

{{CodeSelect|code=
#!/bin/bash
set -x
exec \
find \
"$@" \
-type f \
-not -iwholename '*.git*
}}

Save.

Make executable.

{{CodeSelect|code=
chmod +x ~/bin/myfind
}}

Change directory.

{{CodeSelect|code=
cd {{project_name_short}}
}}

Search for string. For example <code>/etc/apparmor.d</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
myfind . | grep --color -i /etc/apparmor.d
}}

